    "summary": "Experienced HR and Change leader with strong result-oriented approach: 30 years experience in Human Resource Management, Change Management and Organizational Development. Greatly experienced in all aspects of human resources, business improvements and change projects in a variety of organizations. International experience by working with multinationals and frequently speaking in international conferences. \n\nFounder and chairperson of the Innovation Platform Rhythmics of Organizational Change and guest speaker for several universities and organizations. A model of organizational rhythmics was developed in the PhD thesis 'Rhythmics of Organizational Change'. The Foundation of Rhythmics of Organizational Change (I-RO) conducts research on the rhythmics of organizational change. The members of this platform are CIO\u2019s and directors HR of companies and professors of several universities. I-RO develops practical and useful rhythmic instruments, for more effective and successful change processes.Worked for several universities and lectured e.g. Cultural Diagnosis of Organizations and Change Management and coached students with their research and theses. Since October 2014 also Professor at the Antwerp Management School and since 2015 also appointed for Webster University and the European Institute for Procurement Management (Shanghai).",
